## üöÄ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- *Android Studio*: Hedgehog | 2023.1.1 or newer
- *JDK*: 17 or higher
- *Min SDK*: 24 (Android 7.0)
- *Target SDK*: 34 (Android 14)

### Backend Setup
1. Clone and set up the backend repository:
cd inegrationbackend-V1-main
npm install

2. Configure environment variables (see backend ENV_SETUP.md)

3. Start the backend server:
npm run start:dev

### Android App Setup

1. *Clone the repository*:
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd AndroidDam-main

2. *Open in Android Studio*:
   - Open Android Studio
   - Select "Open an Existing Project"
   - Navigate to the AndroidDam-main folder

3. *Configure API Base URL*:
   
   Edit app/src/main/java/tn/esprit/dam/data/ApiConfig.kt:
   
   
   // For Android Emulator
   const val API_BASE_URL = "http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1/"
   
   // For Physical Device (replace with your machine's IP)
   // const val API_BASE_URL = "http://192.168.1.100:3001/api/v1/"
   

4. *Sync Gradle*:
   - Click "Sync Project with Gradle Files" in Android Studio
   - Wait for dependencies to download

5. *Run the app*:
   - Connect an Android device or start an emulator
   - Click the "Run" button (or press Shift+F10)

## üìö Key Screens

### Authentication Flow
- *Splash Screen*: Animated welcome screen
- *Onboarding*: 3-screen introduction carousel
- *Login/Signup*: Role-based authentication (Owner, Coach, Referee, Player)
- *Password Recovery*: Secure password reset flow

### Main Features
- *Home*: Personalized dashboard with quick actions
- *Events*: Browse and join tournaments
- *Calendar*: View scheduled matches and events
- *Teams*: Manage team rosters and lineups
- *Social*: Community feed and networking
- *Profile*: User settings and statistics

### Specialized Screens
- *Tournament Creation*: Multi-step tournament setup with bracket generation
- *Match Officiate*: Real-time match event recording (Referee only)
- *Game Plan*: Tactical formation editor (Coach only)
- *Assign Player*: Search and assign players to teams (Owner only)
- *Stadium Management*: Create and manage venues (Owner only)

## üîë User Roles

| Role | Permissions |
|------|------------|
| *Owner* | Full access: Create tournaments, manage teams, assign players, manage stadiums and staff |
| *Coach* | Create game plans, manage assigned teams, view player stats |
| *Referee* | Officiate matches, record events, view assigned tournaments |
| *Player* | Join tournaments, view teams, update profile, social features |

## üéØ API Integration

The app connects to a Node.js/NestJS backend with the following endpoints:

### Authentication
- POST /auth/signup - User registration
- POST /auth/login - User login
- POST /auth/forgot-password - Password recovery
- POST /auth/reset-password - Password reset

### Tournaments (Coupes)
- GET /coupes - List all tournaments
- POST /coupes - Create tournament
- GET /coupes/:id - Get tournament details
- PATCH /coupes/:id - Update tournament
- POST /coupes/:id/join - Join tournament

### Teams (Equipes)
- GET /equipes/membres/:idAcademie/:categorie - Get team members
- GET /equipes/academie/:idAcademie - Get all academy teams
- PATCH /equipes/add-joueur/:idAcademie - Add player to team

### Matches
- GET /match/:coupeId - Get tournament matches
- PATCH /match/:matchId/event - Record match event (goals, cards, etc.)

