PeakPlay - Soccer Academy Management System

A comprehensive Android application for managing soccer academies, tournaments, teams, and player development.

===============================================================================
FEATURES
===============================================================================

For Academy Owners:
- Dashboard with real-time statistics for tournaments, players, and staff
- Tournament Management: Create, manage, and track soccer tournaments
- Team Builder: Organize teams across multiple categories (Kids, Youth, Junior, Senior)
- Player Assignment: Search and assign players to teams
- Stadium Management: Manage multiple stadium locations
- Staff Coordination: Oversee coaches and referees
- Social Feed: Share updates with the community
- Calendar: Schedule and track events

For Coaches:
- View assigned teams and rosters
- Create game plans with formation diagrams
- Track player progress and performance
- Organize lineups and substitutions

For Referees:
- Real-time match event recording (goals, cards, fouls)
- View assigned matches and tournaments
- Record detailed match statistics

For Players:
- Update personal information and stats
- Join tournaments and view team schedules
- Connect with other players and teams
- View personal statistics and achievements

===============================================================================
TECHNICAL DETAILS
===============================================================================

Language: Kotlin
UI Framework: Jetpack Compose
Min Android Version: 7.0 (API 24)
Target Android Version: 14 (API 34)

Key Libraries:
- Jetpack Compose for modern UI
- Retrofit for API calls
- Coil for image loading
- Coroutines for async operations
- Navigation Compose for screen navigation

===============================================================================
GETTING STARTED
===============================================================================

Prerequisites:
- Android Studio Hedgehog (2023.1.1) or newer
- JDK 17 or higher
- Android device or emulator

Backend Setup:
1. Navigate to backend folder: cd inegrationbackend-V1-main
2. Install dependencies: npm install
3. Start server: npm run start:dev

Android App Setup:
1. Open project in Android Studio
2. Configure API URL in ApiConfig.kt:
   - For Emulator: http://10.0.2.2:3001/api/v1/
   - For Physical Device: http://YOUR_IP:3001/api/v1/
3. Sync Gradle files
4. Run the app

